Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g} and @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break the mince up as it cooks, then drain the fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water{75%ml}.

Stir in a knob of @?butter{knob}.

Bring to the boil then simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the rice between #bowls{}.

Top with the Cajun beef.

Enjoy!